//STEPS
let pizzaSteps = ["Pour the flour into a bowl, crumble the yeast inside and pour the water little by little.", "When you have added almost all the water add salt too.", "Knead everything and transfer the dough to the worktop, working it with your hands until it is smooth and homogeneous.", "At this point let it rest on the worktop for about ten minutes, covering it with the bowl.", "Once rested give it a small fold: imagine that the sphere is divided into 4 parts, take the end of each, gently pull it and fold it back towards the center.", "Once made the 4 folds turn it on itself giving it the shape of a sphere.", "Transfer the dough so formed in a bowl, cover with plastic wrap 12 and let rise.", "After the leavening time, the dough will be well swollen, then transfer it to the worktop and as before, lift a flap of dough and bring it inside.", "Turn the dough upside down and proceed with the pirlatura: pirlare the dough means to make it turn with your hands on the work shelf bringing it towards you and then removing it repeatedly until you get a smooth and regular ball.", "Leave for another 30 minutes.", "Turn on the oven bringing the temperature to 250 ³ and operating the static mode.", "Now with a spoon spread the tomato sauce on the pizza, leaving a free edge.", "Bake and cook for about 6 minutes.", "Cut the mozzarella into sticks or fray it with your hands.", "After 6 minutes, bake pizza.", "Place the mozzarella sticks on top and bake for another 6 minutes.", "When it is golden brown, add the basil leaves, if you like a little oil and serve!"]

let tiramisuSteps = ["Prepare the coffee with the mocha, then sweeten to taste and let it cool in a bowl low and wide.", "Separate the eggs by dividing the egg whites from the yolks: whip the yolks with electric whisks, pouring only half a dose of sugar.", "As soon as the mixture has become clear and foamy, add the mascarpone, little by little.", "Clean the whips very well and beat the egg whites. When they are foamy pour the remaining sugar a little at a time.", "Take a spoonful of egg whites and pour into the bowl with the mascarpone cream and mix vigorously with a spatula. Then proceed to add the remaining part of egg whites, gradually stirring very gently from the bottom up. ", "The mascarpone cream is now ready. Spread a generous spoonful on the bottom of a glass baking dish, large 30x19,5cm and distributed well throughout the base. Soak the ladyfingers for a few moments in cold coffee first on one side and then on the other.", "Gradually spread the ladyfingers soaked in the baking dish, trying to arrange them all in one direction, so as to get a first layer of biscuits. Add more mascarpone cream and level it to cover them completely.", "Continue to distribute the ladyfingers soaked in coffee, then make another layer of cream and level the surface well.", "Sprinkle everything with cocoa powder and let firm in the refrigerator for a couple of hours. Your tiramisu is ready to be enjoyed!"]

let lasagnaSteps = ["First peel the onion and chop it finely. Place it in a large pan with some oil let it dry for a few minutes at medium temperature, then add the ground meat.","Add the tomato sauce and a pinch of salt and mix. Leave to cook for 45 minutes.", "Now cut the mozzarella into small pieces. Equip yourself with a large 30x20 cm lasagne pan and spread a layer of sauce on the bottom. Make a first layer of pasta sheets, overlapping them slightly", "Add more sauce, then the grated Parmesan and the mozzarella cubes. Proceed in this way until all the ingredients are used up.", "Remember that the last layer will be composed only of pasta and sauce, grated cheese and mozzarella. Cook in a preheated static oven at 180° for about 45 minutes. Then take it out of the oven and let it rest for a few minutes before cutting and serving your rich baked lasagna!"]

let risottoSteps = ["Peel and finely chop the onion. Pour 25 g of butter into a large pan, then the chopped onion. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally to soften.", "Once browned, you can pour in the Carnaroli rice: the rice will absorb the butter and mix with the onion. When it is toasted and translucent, you can blend with white wine. Let the alcoholic part evaporate for a few moments.", "Pour the very hot broth to cover and continue cooking over high heat, adding hot broth as needed. Gently immerse the pistils in warm water, mix just to bring them to life.", "¾ of the way through cooking, add the saffron pistils with the soaking water: wait a few moments for them to soften, then mix: they will release their scent and colour. When there is one minute left before the rice is cooked, remove the pan from the heat, add about 120 g of butter in pieces, very cold from the fridge, jumbled up.", "Also pour in the grated Parmesan, mix vigorously, so that the very cold butter and cheese create the thermal shock that will promote creaminess and shine to the risotto. Serve the Milanese risotto piping hot!"]

let meatballSteps = ["Cut the breadcrumbs into pieces and pour it into a mixer. Chop everything until the crumb is reduced to crumbs.", "Take the sausages, cut them and mash the meat.", "Pour the sausage and minced meat into a large bowl. Add the parsley, the parmesan and the egg.", "Season with salt and pepper, then continue to knead until you obtain a homogeneous mixture. With the mixture obtained, form spheres weighing 20 grams each.", "As soon as all the meatballs are ready, heat the oil in a non-stick pan and, when the oil is hot, place the meatballs, leaving them to cook on both sides for a couple of minutes. Pour the tomato pulp.", "Also pour in the water, season with salt, flavor with pepper and continue cooking by lowering the heat for 15-20 minutes. Once ready you can enjoy your meatballs with sauce still steaming!"]

let applepieSteps = ["Peel the apples, cut them into wedges and remove the core. Then cut them into thin slices from the short side. Pour the eggs and sugar into a bowl.", "Whip with an electric whisk and add a pinch of salt. Then pour in the butter and cinnamon.", "Add the grated lemon zest and beat again. Sift the flour inside", "Also sift the yeast and mix again with the whisk, adding the milk slowly.", "Pour the apples inside and mix well. Transfer the mixture into a 22cm mold greased and sprinkled with sugar.", "Level the surface and cook in a preheated static oven at 180° for 55 minutes. Sprinkle with icing sugar and serve your apple pie!"]

let fruitSteps = ["Start with the shortcrust pastry: place the flour and icing sugar in a bowl the seeds scraped from a vanilla bean and the cold butter cut into pieces.", "Work the ingredients with your hands until you obtain a sandy mixture, then add the egg yolks and knead again.", "Wrap the obtained dough in cling film and leave to rest in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes. In the meantime, prepare the custard by pouring the milk into a saucepan.", "Flavor by grating the lemon zest, turn the heat on low and bring to the boil. Pour the egg yolks into another larger saucepan, add the sugar and mix. Also add the cornstarch and flour.", "Mix, then add milk and keep mixing. Move everything to the stove and cook the cream, stirring constantly, until it becomes firm. It will take approximately 10 minutes.", "Transfer the cream into a low, wide container, cover it with cling film and let it cool to room temperature; then put it in the fridge to harden. Collect the shortcrust pastry, roll it out on a lightly floured pastry board and cut out a circle approximately 4 mm thick. Lift the disc with a rolling pin and unroll into the 24 cm mould. Roll the rolling pin over the surface to loosen excess.", "Prick the bottom with the tines of a fork and move on to white cooking: this means cooking the base of the tart without filling, in a static oven, already hot at 180°, for about 20/25 minutes. Remove the pastry base from the oven and let it cool.", "Work the cooled cream with a whisk, transfer it into a piping bag and fill the shortcrust pastry shell. Level the surface with the back of a spoon and place the tart in the refrigerator24.", "In the meantime, move on to cleaning and cutting the fruit.", "Move on to the decoration: do it in a not too tidy manner.", "Complete by garnishing with all the fruit left. Here is your fruit tart ready!."]

let capresecSteps = ["Pour the butter into a bowl, half the sugar and the vanilla. Turn the whisk on medium-high speed and after 6-7 minutes add the pinch of salt and the egg yolks.", "After a few minutes the mixture will be very foamy, then turn off the whisk, clean the bowl with a spatula, collecting all the mixture and set aside. In another bowl mix the powders: add the grated chocolate and the powdered almonds and hazelnuts.", "Sift the potato starch and the baking powder and cocoa powder.", "Mix everything well and keep aside. In another bowl, pour the egg whites and the remaining sugar.", "Preheat the oven to 170° in fan mode and start mixing them: add a third of the whipped egg whites to the egg yolk and butter mixture, then a third of the powders.", "Mix well with the spatula, mixing delicately from bottom to top. Gradually add a third of the egg whites and a third of the powders and continue like this until you obtain a uniform dough.", "Pour the smooth and creamy mixture into a 22cm cake tin already buttered and floured with potato starch. Carefully level the surface and cook in a fan oven at 170° for about 45 minutes.", "Once cooked, let the cake cool in the mold, then turn it over and remove from the mold. Then turn it over again onto a plate lined with baking paper and let it cool completely. Once cool, turn the cake over one last time, remove the baking paper and dust the surface with icing sugar. Your caprese cake is ready to be enjoyed!"]

let spaghettiSteps = ["Start by preparing the sauce. Pour the olive oil into a pan together with the peeled and halved garlic clove. After 2 minutes of cooking over high heat, add the peeled tomatoes and season with salt.","Cover with a lid and cook for at least 1 hour over a very low heat: the sauce should simmer gently. Then, remove the garlic and pass the tomatoes through a food mill, so as to obtain a smooth and homogeneous puree.", "Transfer the sauce back to the pan, turn on the heat very low and add the basil leaves. After a few minutes you can turn off the sauce and keep warm. At this point all you have to do is cook the pasta in plenty of boiling, salted water.", "Drain the spaghetti directly into the sauce and stir for a few moments over high heat to mix everything together. Your spaghetti with tomato sauce is ready, all you have to do is plate it and garnish with fresh basil as desired!"]

let babaSteps = ["Pour the flour into a planetary mixer, together with sugar and cold butter cut into pieces.","Add the yeast and 3 cold eggs, a little at a time. Start kneading at medium-low speed: the dough must completely absorb the eggs.", "Always add the salt with the planetary mixer running, then knead for another 5-10 minutes. Once the dough has formed, remove it from the hook and give it a spherical shape, then cover with cling film and leave to rise for about 2 hours, away from drafts. It should double in volume.", "In the meantime you can prepare the syrup which needs more rest, and which will be used to wet the babas before serving them. Pour the water and sugar into a saucepan10and bring to the boil. Turn off and let cool completely. Only when it is cold can you add the 70° rum. Keep the syrup aside.", "Meanwhile, resume working the dough: add the other 3 eggs to the planetary mixer little by little. It will take at least 30-40 minutes for all the eggs to be fully incorporated.", "Once the dough is ready, oil the molds with a capacity of approximately 70 g, then lightly oil the work surface.", "Turn the dough out onto the work surface, give just a few folds to reinforce it and then, to make a morsel of around 30-40 g at a time, pull an edge of the dough with one hand and squeeze to let it come out between your index finger and thumb, with your hand closed. Place each piece in the oiled molds, which you will have placed on a baking tray.", "With these doses you will obtain 10-12 babas. You will then have to let them rise without covering them, in the oven turned off with the light on (about 26°) until they have reached the edge of the mold. Cook in a preheated static oven at 200° for approximately 15-20 minutes. Once cooked, let them cool to room temperature, then remove them from the mold and leave them to air dry for up to 24 hours.", "To make the ponch that will be used to soak the babà, pour water and sugar into a large pan and bring to the boil. Turn off the heat and flavor with orange zest and lemon.", "When the syrup has cooled, remove the peels and pour in the 70° rum, then mix.", "Transfer the syrup you had previously prepared into a bottle. Dip the babas in the ponch and leave them to soak for 2-3 minutes.", "Squeeze the babà lightly and place them to drain on a wire rack under which you have placed a tray to collect excess liquid. Before serving, sprinkle each babà with the prepared syrup and it will be ready to be enjoyed!"]

let carbonaraSteps = [ "Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.",
    "Cook the spaghetti according to package instructions until 'al dente'.",
    "Meanwhile, cut the guanciale into small strips or cubes.",
    "In a large skillet, cook the guanciale over medium heat until crispy and golden brown. Remove from the skillet and set aside.",
    "In a mixing bowl, whisk together the eggs, grated Pecorino Romano cheese, and a generous amount of freshly ground black pepper.",
    "Once the spaghetti is cooked, reserve a cup of pasta cooking water, then drain the spaghetti and return it to the pot.",
    "Working quickly, add the cooked guanciale to the pot with the spaghetti, then pour the egg and cheese mixture over the top.",
    "Toss the spaghetti with the egg mixture, using tongs to evenly coat the pasta. If needed, add a splash of reserved pasta cooking water to loosen the sauce.",
    "Continue tossing until the sauce thickens and coats the spaghetti.",
    "Serve immediately, garnished with additional grated Pecorino Romano cheese and black pepper, if desired."
]

let eggplantSteps = [
