let pastieraSteps = [
    "Start by preparing the wheat. Rinse them under cold water, then soak them in water overnight.",
    "The next day, drain the wheat and place it in a large pot. Cover them with water and simmer over low heat for about 2-3 hours, or until they are soft. Make sure to stir occasionally and add more water if needed. Once cooked, drain any excess water and let the wheat cool.",
    "Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease and flour a 9-inch round cake pan or line it with parchment paper.",
    "Roll out the shortcrust pastry sheet and use it to line the prepared cake pan, making sure to trim any excess pastry.",
    "In a saucepan, heat the whole milk over medium heat until it begins to simmer. Add the cooked wheat and cook for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens.",
    "Remove the saucepan from the heat and let the mixture cool slightly.",
    "In a large mixing bowl, beat the eggs with the granulated sugar until pale and fluffy.",
    "Add the ricotta cheese, orange zest, lemon zest, and vanilla extract to the egg mixture. Mix until well combined.",
    "Fold in the cooked wheat mixture, diced candied citron, diced candied orange peel, and ground cinnamon until evenly distributed.",
    "Pour the filling into the prepared pastry-lined cake pan, spreading it out evenly.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for about 1 hour, or until the top is golden brown and the filling is set. If the top starts to brown too quickly, you can cover the cake loosely with aluminum foil.",
    "Once baked, remove the pastiera from the oven and let it cool completely in the pan.",
    "Once cooled, carefully remove the pastiera from the pan and transfer it to a serving plate.",
    "Dust the top of the pastiera with powdered sugar if desired.",
    "Slice and serve the pastiera at room temperature, and enjoy this delicious traditional Italian Easter cake!"
]

let gnocchiSteps = [
    "First, wash and scrub the potatoes thoroughly to remove any dirt. Leave the skin on to help retain moisture during cooking.",
    "Place the whole potatoes in a large pot and cover them with cold water. Bring the water to a boil over medium-high heat, then reduce the heat to low and let the potatoes simmer for about 45-50 minutes, or until they are fork-tender.",
    "Once cooked, drain the potatoes and let them cool for a few minutes until they are cool enough to handle but still warm.",
    "Peel the potatoes while they are still warm. The skin should easily come off. Discard the skins and transfer the peeled potatoes to a large mixing bowl.",
    "Mash the potatoes using a potato masher or a fork until they are smooth and lump-free. It's important to work quickly while the potatoes are still warm to prevent them from becoming gummy.",
    "Let the mashed potatoes cool completely before proceeding to the next step.",
    "Once the mashed potatoes are cool, add the beaten egg and salt to the bowl. Mix until well combined.",
    "Gradually add the flour to the potato mixture, stirring with a wooden spoon or your hands, until a soft dough forms. Be careful not to overwork the dough, as this can make the gnocchi tough. You may not need to use all of the flour.",
    "Transfer the dough to a floured work surface and gently knead it a few times until it comes together into a smooth ball.",
    "Divide the dough into smaller portions and roll each portion into a long rope, about 1/2 inch in diameter.",
    "Using a sharp knife, cut the ropes of dough into bite-sized pieces, about 1 inch long. You can leave them as is or roll them over the tines of a fork to create ridges, which will help the sauce cling to the gnocchi.",
    "Once all the gnocchi are shaped, you can cook them immediately in boiling salted water, or you can freeze them for later use.",
    "To cook the gnocchi, bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Gently drop the gnocchi into the boiling water, working in batches if necessary to avoid overcrowding the pot.",
    "Cook the gnocchi for about 2-3 minutes, or until they float to the surface. Once they float, let them cook for an additional 30 seconds to 1 minute.",
    "Using a slotted spoon or spider strainer, remove the cooked gnocchi from the water and transfer them to a serving dish. Repeat until all the gnocchi are cooked.",
    "Serve the gnocchi hot with your favorite sauce, such as marinara, pesto, or brown butter sage sauce. Enjoy your delicious homemade gnocchi!"
]

let tagliatelleSteps = [
    "On a clean work surface, pour the all-purpose flour and create a well in the center.",
    "Crack the eggs into the well and add the salt and olive oil.",
    "Using a fork, gradually incorporate the flour into the eggs, starting from the inside of the well and working your way outwards. Continue mixing until a dough forms.",
    "Once the dough comes together, knead it for about 8-10 minutes until it becomes smooth and elastic. You can sprinkle a little extra flour on the work surface if the dough is too sticky.",
    "Shape the dough into a ball and wrap it tightly in plastic wrap. Let it rest at room temperature for about 30 minutes to allow the gluten to relax.",
    "After the resting period, divide the dough into smaller portions. Work with one portion at a time, keeping the rest covered with a clean kitchen towel or plastic wrap to prevent drying out.",
    "Using a rolling pin or pasta machine, roll out the dough into a thin sheet, about 1-2 mm thick. Dust the dough with flour as needed to prevent sticking.",
    "Once you have rolled out the dough, use a sharp knife or a pasta cutter to cut the sheet of dough into long strips, about 1/4 to 1/2 inch wide for tagliatelle.",
    "Gently toss the cut strips of pasta with a little extra flour to prevent them from sticking together.",
    "To cook the tagliatelle, bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add the pasta and cook for about 2-3 minutes, or until al dente. Fresh pasta cooks much faster than dried pasta, so keep an eye on it.",
    "Once the pasta is cooked, drain it using a colander and toss it immediately with your favorite sauce. Serve hot and enjoy your homemade tagliatelle!"
]

let lemonSteps = [
    "Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease and flour a 9-inch round cake pan or line it with parchment paper.",
    "In a large mixing bowl, cream together the softened unsalted butter and granulated sugar until light and fluffy.",
    "Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.",
    "In a separate bowl, sift together the all-purpose flour, baking powder, and salt.",
    "Add the lemon zest to the dry ingredients and mix to combine.",
    "In another bowl, combine the lemon juice and whole milk.",
    "Alternate adding the dry ingredients and the lemon juice-milk mixture to the butter-sugar mixture, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients. Mix until just combined, being careful not to overmix.",
    "Pour the batter into the prepared cake pan and spread it out evenly.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for about 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.",
    "Remove the cake from the oven and let it cool in the pan for about 10 minutes.",
    "Once cooled slightly, transfer the cake to a wire rack to cool completely.",
    "Once the cake has cooled, dust the top with powdered sugar.",
    "Slice and serve the Delizia al Limone cake, and enjoy its bright and citrusy flavor!"
]

let pannaCottaSteps = [
    "In a small bowl, sprinkle the gelatin over the cold water. Let it sit for about 5-10 minutes to soften.",
    "In a saucepan, combine the heavy cream, milk, and granulated sugar. Place the saucepan over medium heat and bring the mixture to a simmer, stirring occasionally to dissolve the sugar.",
    "Once the mixture is simmering and the sugar has dissolved, remove the saucepan from the heat.",
    "Add the softened gelatin to the warm cream mixture and stir until the gelatin is completely dissolved.",
    "Stir in the vanilla extract until well combined.",
    "Divide the mixture evenly among 4 serving glasses or ramekins.",
    "Let the Panna Cotta cool to room temperature, then cover each glass or ramekin with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, or until set.",
    "Once set, remove the Panna Cotta from the refrigerator and serve chilled, either in the glasses or ramekins or unmolded onto serving plates.",
    "Garnish with fresh berries, if desired, and enjoy your creamy and delicious Panna Cotta!"
]

let pestoSteps = [
